</poem>
</div2>
<div2>
<poem><comhd2 r="italic"><idref>Z200546931</idref><collection>1 2</collection>

<somhead><somauth>Ashby, Cliff.<sombiog>168</sombiog></somauth><mainhead>I Would Not Ask</mainhead> <attbytes>1Kb</attbytes><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></somhead><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>DATA</TY><ID>Z200546931</ID><A1>Ashby, Cliff.</A1><T1>I Would Not Ask</T1><PBL>Carcanet</PBL><Y1>1985</Y1><T2>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)</T2><T3>Literature Online</T3></comcitn></comhd2>
<attribs><attpoet>Ashby, Cliff.</attpoet><attidref>X2000096</attidref></attribs>
<newatts><attidref>X2000096</attidref><attdbase>Modern Poetry</attdbase><attdbase>Twentieth-Century English Poetry</attdbase><attpubl>Carcanet</attpubl><atttitle><mainhead>I Would Not Ask</mainhead><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></atttitle><attsize>1Kb</attsize><attperi>Twentieth-Century 1900-1999</attperi><attpubn1>1985</attpubn1><attpubn2>1985</attpubn2><attview></attview><attview><engcorp2></engcorp2></attview><attautid>168</attautid></newatts>
<pdiv><firstl><l ln="1        ">I would not ask</l></firstl>
<l ln="2        ">For I would not expect</l>
<l ln="3        ">The Son of God</l>
<l ln="4        ">To live within the confines</l>
<l ln="5        ">Of these shabby clothes.</l>
<l ln="6        ">Nor that His love would stray</l>
<l ln="7        ">Into the clapped out</l>
<l ln="8        ">Ventricles of this heart</l>
<l ln="9        ">And flower in my blood</l>
<l ln="10      ">As love.</l></pdiv>
<pdiv><l ln="11      ">&indent;Wind whips down the river</l>
<l ln="12      ">&indent;I feel the pulsing in my ribs</l>
<l ln="13      ">&indent;Night finds me unprepared.</l></pdiv>
<poemcopy>&copy; Copyright material reproduced under licence from Carcanet Press Ltd.</poemcopy>
</poem>
</div2>
<div2>
<poem><comhd2 r="italic"><idref>Z200546932</idref><collection>1 2</collection>

<somhead><somauth>Ashby, Cliff.<sombiog>168</sombiog></somauth><mainhead>Naked</mainhead> <attbytes>1Kb</attbytes><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></somhead><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>DATA</TY><ID>Z200546932</ID><A1>Ashby, Cliff.</A1><T1>Naked</T1><PBL>Carcanet</PBL><Y1>1985</Y1><T2>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)</T2><T3>Literature Online</T3></comcitn></comhd2>
<attribs><attpoet>Ashby, Cliff.</attpoet><attidref>X2000097</attidref></attribs>
<newatts><attidref>X2000097</attidref><attdbase>Modern Poetry</attdbase><attdbase>Twentieth-Century English Poetry</attdbase><attpubl>Carcanet</attpubl><atttitle><mainhead>Naked</mainhead><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></atttitle><attsize>1Kb</attsize><attperi>Twentieth-Century 1900-1999</attperi><attpubn1>1985</attpubn1><attpubn2>1985</attpubn2><attview></attview><attview><engcorp2></engcorp2></attview><attautid>168</attautid></newatts>
<firstl><l ln="1        ">The sun catches the pink</l></firstl>
<l ln="2        ">Of the azaleas.</l>
<l ln="3        ">All through the winter</l>
<l ln="4        ">Heart as black as pitch</l>
<l ln="5        ">I have groped within my box of pills</l>
<l ln="6        ">Searching for salvation&mdash;</l>
<l ln="7        ">The bowels of Christ denied me this.</l>
<l ln="8        ">Young man I laid upon the ground,</l>
<pb n="132">
<l ln="9        ">If God saw violence then I would be violent,</l>
<l ln="10      ">Beating the stones with bruised and bloody fists</l>
<l ln="11      ">But the Keeper of the Gate remained unmoved.</l>
<l ln="12      ">&indent;I rose up from the earth strangely chastened.</l>
<poemcopy>&copy; Copyright material reproduced under licence from Carcanet Press Ltd.</poemcopy>
</poem>
</div2>
<div2>
<poem><comhd2 r="italic"><idref>Z200546933</idref><collection>1 2</collection>

<somhead><somauth>Ashby, Cliff.<sombiog>168</sombiog></somauth><mainhead>With Roughened Sighs</mainhead> <attbytes>1Kb</attbytes><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></somhead><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>DATA</TY><ID>Z200546933</ID><A1>Ashby, Cliff.</A1><T1>With Roughened Sighs</T1><PBL>Carcanet</PBL><Y1>1985</Y1><T2>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)</T2><T3>Literature Online</T3></comcitn></comhd2>
<attribs><attpoet>Ashby, Cliff.</attpoet><attidref>X2000098</attidref></attribs>
<newatts><attidref>X2000098</attidref><attdbase>Modern Poetry</attdbase><attdbase>Twentieth-Century English Poetry</attdbase><attpubl>Carcanet</attpubl><atttitle><mainhead>With Roughened Sighs</mainhead><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></atttitle><attsize>1Kb</attsize><attperi>Twentieth-Century 1900-1999</attperi><attpubn1>1985</attpubn1><attpubn2>1985</attpubn2><attview></attview><attview><engcorp2></engcorp2></attview><attautid>168</attautid></newatts>
<firstl><l ln="1        ">With roughened sighs</l></firstl>
<l ln="2        ">The East Wind snores and snuffles</l>
<l ln="3        ">Through the ginnel.</l>
<l ln="4        ">From Bob's Emporium</l>
<l ln="5        ">The smell of frying fish</l>
<l ln="6        ">Batters my person.</l>
<l ln="7        ">A bicycle tyre hangs</l>
<l ln="8        ">From a lamp post</l>
<l ln="9        ">Bowed in silent prayer.</l>
<l ln="10      ">Night, the frost nibbles</l>
<l ln="11      ">At the hem of my distress.</l>
<poemcopy>&copy; Copyright material reproduced under licence from Carcanet Press Ltd.</poemcopy>
</poem>
</div2>
<div2>
<poem><comhd2 r="italic"><idref>Z200546934</idref><collection>1 2</collection>

<somhead><somauth>Ashby, Cliff.<sombiog>168</sombiog></somauth><mainhead>Unpopular Opinions</mainhead> <attbytes>2Kb</attbytes><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></somhead><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>DATA</TY><ID>Z200546934</ID><A1>Ashby, Cliff.</A1><T1>Unpopular Opinions</T1><PBL>Carcanet</PBL><Y1>1985</Y1><T2>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)</T2><T3>Literature Online</T3></comcitn></comhd2>
<attribs><attpoet>Ashby, Cliff.</attpoet><attidref>X2000099</attidref></attribs>
<newatts><attidref>X2000099</attidref><attdbase>Modern Poetry</attdbase><attdbase>Twentieth-Century English Poetry</attdbase><attpubl>Carcanet</attpubl><atttitle><mainhead>Unpopular Opinions</mainhead><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></atttitle><attsize>2Kb</attsize><attperi>Twentieth-Century 1900-1999</attperi><attpubn1>1985</attpubn1><attpubn2>1985</attpubn2><attview></attview><attview><engcorp2></engcorp2></attview><attautid>168</attautid></newatts>
<firstl><l ln="1        ">Delicate Dale and cosy Cookson</l></firstl>
<l ln="2        ">Print their arty, bow&hyphen;tied stuff</l>
<l ln="3        ">And the poems in PNR?</l>
<l ln="4        ">One cannot say they're up to snuff!</l>
<l ln="5        ">Something's vanished from the language</l>
<l ln="6        ">Once so vigorous and grand</l>
<l ln="7        ">And what's left is pap and pobbies</l>
<l ln="8        ">Neatly writ&mdash;but very bland.</l>
<l ln="9        ">John Skelton once gave birth to words</l>
<l ln="10      ">Undisciplined but full of power</l>
<l ln="11      ">As though they were being coined and cast</l>
<l ln="12      ">To legal currency by the hour.</l>
<l ln="13      ">And Anon like an honest man</l>
<pb n="133">
<l ln="14      ">Declined to pretty up and say</l>
<l ln="15      ">What happened to A Serving Girl</l>
<l ln="16      ">Upon Her Holiday.</l>
<l ln="17      ">Indeed it never would occur</l>
<l ln="18      ">To boil the good red meat to jelly</l>
<l ln="19      ">But tell the tale of chest to tit</l>
<l ln="20      ">And cock to cunt and belly to belly.</l>
<l ln="21      ">At later date poor mad mild Clare</l>
<l ln="22      ">Put sweeter songs in a thrushes throat</l>
<l ln="23      ">But Hardy, Barnes and Edward Thomas</l>
<l ln="24      ">Left thin grey tack in the gravy boat.</l>
<l ln="25      ">Well to be fair the times had changed</l>
<l ln="26      ">They couldn't say again</l>
<l ln="27      ">What had been said by better poets&mdash;</l>
<l ln="28      ">But they were gentlemen</l>
<l ln="29      ">And no one would deny or try</l>
<l ln="30      ">To doubt their capability</l>
<l ln="31      ">But what comes out is mainly</l>
<l ln="32      ">A middle&hyphen;class sensibility.</l>
<poemcopy>&copy; Copyright material reproduced under licence from Carcanet Press Ltd.</poemcopy>
</poem>
</div2>
<div2>
<poem><comhd2 r="italic"><idref>Z200546935</idref><collection>1 2</collection>

<somhead><somauth>Ashby, Cliff.<sombiog>168</sombiog></somauth><mainhead>Latter Day Psalm</mainhead> <attbytes>1Kb</attbytes><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></somhead><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>DATA</TY><ID>Z200546935</ID><A1>Ashby, Cliff.</A1><T1>Latter Day Psalm</T1><PBL>Carcanet</PBL><Y1>1985</Y1><T2>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)</T2><T3>Literature Online</T3></comcitn></comhd2>
<attribs><attpoet>Ashby, Cliff.</attpoet><attidref>X2000100</attidref></attribs>
<newatts><attidref>X2000100</attidref><attdbase>Modern Poetry</attdbase><attdbase>Twentieth-Century English Poetry</attdbase><attpubl>Carcanet</attpubl><atttitle><mainhead>Latter Day Psalm</mainhead><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></atttitle><attsize>1Kb</attsize><attperi>Twentieth-Century 1900-1999</attperi><attpubn1>1985</attpubn1><attpubn2>1985</attpubn2><attview></attview><attview><engcorp2></engcorp2></attview><attautid>168</attautid></newatts>
<firstl><l ln="1        ">Search out my blemishes, Lord</l></firstl>
<l ln="2        ">Investigate these bones,</l>
<l ln="3        ">For my head is full of shadows</l>
<l ln="4        ">And through the channels of my blood</l>
<l ln="5        ">Fear runs amuck.</l>
<l ln="6        ">When I would speak with you</l>
<l ln="7        ">What dribbles from my tongue</l>
<l ln="8        ">Are stale requests.</l>
<l ln="9        ">&indent;Insinuate the crevices of my mind</l>
<l ln="10      ">Remove the evil vestments from my heart</l>
<l ln="11      ">For my eyes cannot see God</l>
<l ln="12      ">My ears dull to His word</l>
<l ln="13      ">There is no pleasure in my children.</l>
<poemcopy>&copy; Copyright material reproduced under licence from Carcanet Press Ltd.</poemcopy>
</poem>
</div2>
<pb n="134">
<div2>
<poem><comhd2 r="italic"><idref>Z200546936</idref><collection>1 2</collection>

<somhead><somauth>Ashby, Cliff.<sombiog>168</sombiog></somauth><mainhead>A View</mainhead> <attbytes>2Kb</attbytes><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></somhead><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>DATA</TY><ID>Z200546936</ID><A1>Ashby, Cliff.</A1><T1>A View</T1><PBL>Carcanet</PBL><Y1>1985</Y1><T2>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)</T2><T3>Literature Online</T3></comcitn></comhd2>
<attribs><attpoet>Ashby, Cliff.</attpoet><attidref>X2000101</attidref></attribs>
<newatts><attidref>X2000101</attidref><attdbase>Modern Poetry</attdbase><attdbase>Twentieth-Century English Poetry</attdbase><attpubl>Carcanet</attpubl><atttitle><mainhead>A View</mainhead><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></atttitle><attsize>2Kb</attsize><attperi>Twentieth-Century 1900-1999</attperi><attpubn1>1985</attpubn1><attpubn2>1985</attpubn2><attview></attview><attview><engcorp2></engcorp2></attview><attautid>168</attautid></newatts>
<div3><comhd3><idref>Z300546937</idref><collection>1 2</collection>

1 <attbytes>1Kb</attbytes><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>DATA</TY><ID>Z300546937</ID><A1>Ashby, Cliff.</A1><T1>A View</T1><PBL>Carcanet</PBL><Y1>1985</Y1><T2>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)</T2><T3>Literature Online</T3></comcitn></comhd3>
<pdiv><firstl><l ln="1        ">I have sat watching</l></firstl>
<l ln="2        ">Many Sunday nights</l>
<l ln="3        ">Ecstasy on the face</l>
<l ln="4        ">Of well&hyphen;dressed women</l>
<l ln="5        ">Singing the Sabbath hymns.</l></pdiv>
<pdiv><l ln="6        ">Or</l></pdiv>
<pdiv><l ln="7        ">Noticed while walking</l>
<l ln="8        ">Hopton Woods</l>
<l ln="9        ">The sexuality of trees.</l>
<l ln="10      ">Seen sallow sun</l>
<l ln="11      ">Emerge from winter sky</l>
<l ln="12      ">And light a spirit</l>
<l ln="13      ">That had dropped to earth.</l></pdiv></div3>
<div3><comhd3><idref>Z300546938</idref><collection>1 2</collection>

2 <attbytes>1Kb</attbytes><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>DATA</TY><ID>Z300546938</ID><A1>Ashby, Cliff.</A1><T1>A View</T1><PBL>Carcanet</PBL><Y1>1985</Y1><T2>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)</T2><T3>Literature Online</T3></comcitn></comhd3>
<l ln="14      ">This man</l>
<l ln="15      ">Turning into himself</l>
<l ln="16      ">Found</l>
<l ln="17      ">A stranger with</l>
<l ln="18      ">A cloven hoof.</l>
<l ln="19      ">That man</l>
<l ln="20      ">Exploring in</l>
<l ln="21      ">An uncaring world</l>
<l ln="22      ">Drowned</l>
<l ln="23      ">In his own distractions.</l></div3>
<poemcopy>&copy; Copyright material reproduced under licence from Carcanet Press Ltd.</poemcopy>
</poem>
</div2>
<div2>
<poem><comhd2><idref>Z200546939</idref><collection>1 2</collection>

<somhead><somauth>Ashby, Cliff.<sombiog>168</sombiog></somauth><mainhead><hi r="italic">Poem</hi> [My voice has lost its Frank Sinatra feeling]</mainhead> <attbytes>1Kb</attbytes><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></somhead><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>DATA</TY><ID>Z200546939</ID><A1>Ashby, Cliff.</A1><T1>Poem [My voice has lost its Frank Sinatra feeling]</T1><PBL>Carcanet</PBL><Y1>1985</Y1><T2>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)</T2><T3>Literature Online</T3></comcitn></comhd2>
<attribs><attpoet>Ashby, Cliff.</attpoet><attidref>X2000102</attidref></attribs>
<newatts><attidref>X2000102</attidref><attdbase>Modern Poetry</attdbase><attdbase>Twentieth-Century English Poetry</attdbase><attpubl>Carcanet</attpubl><atttitle><mainhead>Poem [My voice has lost its Frank Sinatra feeling]</mainhead><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></atttitle><attsize>1Kb</attsize><attperi>Twentieth-Century 1900-1999</attperi><attpubn1>1985</attpubn1><attpubn2>1985</attpubn2><attview></attview><attview><engcorp2></engcorp2></attview><attautid>168</attautid></newatts>
<firstl><l ln="1        ">My voice has lost its Frank Sinatra feeling</l></firstl>
<l ln="2        ">My trumpet imitations now sound flat,</l>
<l ln="3        ">I have no moral feelings about stealing</l>
<l ln="4        ">I eat and drink less yet I still grow fat.</l>
<pb n="135">
<l ln="5        ">The love I once gave gladly to my brother</l>
<l ln="6        ">I find now hardly stretches to my dog,</l>
<l ln="7        ">I don't suppose we really like each other</l>
<l ln="8        ">There's not enough affection left to log.</l>
<l ln="9        ">Too man &ldquo;I's&rdquo; too many &ldquo;my's&rdquo; so selfish</l>
<l ln="10      ">They punctuate the rhythm pride has played,</l>
<l ln="11      ">My outer surfaces rival the shellfish</l>
<l ln="12      ">Hate lingers, O&mdash;I wish that love had stayed.</l>
<poemcopy>&copy; Copyright material reproduced under licence from Carcanet Press Ltd.</poemcopy>
</poem>
</div2>
<div2>
<poem><comhd2 r="italic"><idref>Z200546940</idref><collection>1 2</collection>

<somhead><somauth>Ashby, Cliff.<sombiog>168</sombiog></somauth><mainhead>An Exercise in Trivia</mainhead> <attbytes>2Kb</attbytes><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></somhead><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>DATA</TY><ID>Z200546940</ID><A1>Ashby, Cliff.</A1><T1>An Exercise in Trivia</T1><PBL>Carcanet</PBL><Y1>1985</Y1><T2>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)</T2><T3>Literature Online</T3></comcitn></comhd2>
<attribs><attpoet>Ashby, Cliff.</attpoet><attidref>X2000103</attidref></attribs>
<newatts><attidref>X2000103</attidref><attdbase>Modern Poetry</attdbase><attdbase>Twentieth-Century English Poetry</attdbase><attpubl>Carcanet</attpubl><atttitle><mainhead>An Exercise in Trivia</mainhead><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></atttitle><attsize>2Kb</attsize><attperi>Twentieth-Century 1900-1999</attperi><attpubn1>1985</attpubn1><attpubn2>1985</attpubn2><attview></attview><attview><engcorp2></engcorp2></attview><attautid>168</attautid></newatts>
<firstl><l ln="1        ">The cabbage whites that flutter</l></firstl>
<l ln="2        ">Round the washing on this</l>
<l ln="3        ">Limp June day, seem as uncertain</l>
<l ln="4        ">Where to go as I am doubtful</l>
<l ln="5        ">What to say. The woman striding</l>
<l ln="6        ">Down the path, &ldquo;O&rdquo; levels finished</l>
<l ln="7        ">Yesterday, has hung her blazer</l>
<l ln="8        ">Up for good and gone to work at</l>
<l ln="9        ">Lesstopay. These observations</l>
<l ln="10      ">May not please the poets discussing</l>
<l ln="11      ">Overly&mdash;they haven't got a</l>
<l ln="12      ">Lot of wit&mdash;life's ecstasy and</l>
<l ln="13      ">Agony. May I just say in</l>
<l ln="14      ">Manner mild, that on this point I</l>
<l ln="15      ">Do agree, but one has got to</l>
<l ln="16      ">Pass the time between the morning</l>
<l ln="17      ">Meal and tea. Of course I could have</l>
<l ln="18      ">Clipped the hedge, in fact I tried and</l>
<l ln="19      ">Hurt my beck, oh what a beautiful</l>
<l ln="20      ">Excuse to wander down and</l>
<l ln="21      ">See the quack. The other week I</l>
<l ln="22      ">Noticed that he'd bought a spanking new</l>
<l ln="23      ">Mercedes, purchased by seeing</l>
<l ln="24      ">Nuts like me, and reassuring preg&hyphen;</l>
<l ln="25      ">Nant ladies. Last time I saw him</l>
<pb n="136">
<l ln="26      ">He remarked, &ldquo;You seem a lit&hyphen;</l>
<l ln="27      ">Tle thinner,&rdquo; I would write more but</l>
<l ln="28      ">Ann has knocked to say it's time</l>
<l ln="29      ">For dinner.</l>
<poemcopy>&copy; Copyright material reproduced under licence from Carcanet Press Ltd.</poemcopy>
</poem>
</div2>
<div2>
<poem><comhd2 r="italic"><idref>Z200546941</idref><collection>1 2</collection>

<somhead><somauth>Ashby, Cliff.<sombiog>168</sombiog></somauth><mainhead>A Tribute</mainhead> <attbytes>2Kb</attbytes><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></somhead><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>DATA</TY><ID>Z200546941</ID><A1>Ashby, Cliff.</A1><T1>A Tribute</T1><PBL>Carcanet</PBL><Y1>1985</Y1><T2>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)</T2><T3>Literature Online</T3></comcitn></comhd2>
<attribs><attpoet>Ashby, Cliff.</attpoet><attidref>X2000104</attidref></attribs>
<newatts><attidref>X2000104</attidref><attdbase>Modern Poetry</attdbase><attdbase>Twentieth-Century English Poetry</attdbase><attpubl>Carcanet</attpubl><atttitle><mainhead>A Tribute</mainhead><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></atttitle><attsize>2Kb</attsize><attperi>Twentieth-Century 1900-1999</attperi><attpubn1>1985</attpubn1><attpubn2>1985</attpubn2><attview></attview><attview><engcorp2></engcorp2></attview><attautid>168</attautid></newatts>
<dedicat r="italic">for C.H. Sisson's Seventieth Birthday</dedicat>
<firstl><l ln="1        ">His real ambition was</l></firstl>
<l ln="2        ">To nurture things, not people</l>
<l ln="3        ">Though he did this too.</l>
<l ln="4        ">Like the grave his heart</l>
<l ln="5        ">Is a private place where emotion</l>
<l ln="6        ">Is deliberately kept at a low temperature.</l>
<l ln="7        ">So writing verse fulfilled, to some degree</l>
<l ln="8        ">His farming instincts.</l>
<l ln="9        ">I have watched him</l>
<l ln="10      ">In his garden turning soil</l>
<l ln="11      ">And wondered what flowering</l>
<l ln="12      ">Might emerge from this</l>
<l ln="13      ">Well tendered tilth.</l>
<l ln="14      ">A poet of the overlooked</l>
<l ln="15      ">His poems resound with bells</l>
<l ln="16      ">Sun scented blooms</l>
<l ln="17      ">Small shells and birdsong.</l>
<l ln="18      ">Even the empty air</l>
<l ln="19      ">Is filled with wonder</l>
<l ln="20      ">As he milks the muse</l>
<l ln="21      ">With tender dedication.</l>
<poemcopy>&copy; Copyright material reproduced under licence from Carcanet Press Ltd.</poemcopy>
</poem>
</div2>
<pb n="137">
<div2>
<poem><comhd2><idref>Z200546942</idref><collection>1 2</collection>

<somhead><somauth>Ashby, Cliff.<sombiog>168</sombiog></somauth><mainhead><hi r="italic">Poem</hi> [Poor young girl]</mainhead> <attbytes>1Kb</attbytes><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></somhead><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>DATA</TY><ID>Z200546942</ID><A1>Ashby, Cliff.</A1><T1>Poem [Poor young girl]</T1><PBL>Carcanet</PBL><Y1>1985</Y1><T2>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)</T2><T3>Literature Online</T3></comcitn></comhd2>
