<div2>
<poem><comhd2 r="italic"><idref>Z200546962</idref><collection>1 2</collection>

<somhead><somauth>Ashby, Cliff.<sombiog>168</sombiog></somauth><mainhead>Thoughts on a Sleepless Night</mainhead> <attbytes>1Kb</attbytes><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></somhead><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>DATA</TY><ID>Z200546962</ID><A1>Ashby, Cliff.</A1><T1>Thoughts on a Sleepless Night</T1><PBL>Carcanet</PBL><Y1>1985</Y1><T2>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)</T2><T3>Literature Online</T3></comcitn></comhd2>
<attribs><attpoet>Ashby, Cliff.</attpoet><attidref>X2000125</attidref></attribs>
<newatts><attidref>X2000125</attidref><attdbase>Modern Poetry</attdbase><attdbase>Twentieth-Century English Poetry</attdbase><attpubl>Carcanet</attpubl><atttitle><mainhead>Thoughts on a Sleepless Night</mainhead><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></atttitle><attsize>1Kb</attsize><attperi>Twentieth-Century 1900-1999</attperi><attpubn1>1985</attpubn1><attpubn2>1985</attpubn2><attview></attview><attview><engcorp2></engcorp2></attview><attautid>168</attautid></newatts>
<firstl><l ln="1        ">I will stand among the flowers</l></firstl>
<l ln="2        ">And let the August wind brush against my cheeks.</l>
<l ln="3        ">Night, and all the senses ask for sleep</l>
<l ln="4        ">To place a cooling hand upon the forehead.</l>
<l ln="5        ">The air so dry grit makes the eye abrasive</l>
<l ln="6        ">Seeding rosebay clutches at one's hair.</l>
<l ln="7        ">Somewhere behind me in the window box</l>
<l ln="8        ">The succulent stemmed begonias dance</l>
<l ln="9        ">In an erotic tremor.</l>
<l ln="10      ">A distant train disturbs the insomniacs' silence</l>
<l ln="11      ">Mrs Patel's child whimpers in her dream.</l>
<poemcopy>&copy; Copyright material reproduced under licence from Carcanet Press Ltd.</poemcopy>
</poem>
</div2>
<div2>
<poem><comhd2 r="italic"><idref>Z200546963</idref><collection>1 2</collection>

<somhead><somauth>Ashby, Cliff.<sombiog>168</sombiog></somauth><mainhead>Dear</mainhead> <attbytes>1Kb</attbytes><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></somhead><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>DATA</TY><ID>Z200546963</ID><A1>Ashby, Cliff.</A1><T1>Dear</T1><PBL>Carcanet</PBL><Y1>1985</Y1><T2>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)</T2><T3>Literature Online</T3></comcitn></comhd2>
<attribs><attpoet>Ashby, Cliff.</attpoet><attidref>X2000126</attidref></attribs>
<newatts><attidref>X2000126</attidref><attdbase>Modern Poetry</attdbase><attdbase>Twentieth-Century English Poetry</attdbase><attpubl>Carcanet</attpubl><atttitle><mainhead>Dear</mainhead><volhead>Plain Song: Collected Poems: 1960&ndash;1985 (1985)<publish>, Carcanet</publish></volhead></atttitle><attsize>1Kb</attsize><attperi>Twentieth-Century 1900-1999</attperi><attpubn1>1985</attpubn1><attpubn2>1985</attpubn2><attview></attview><attview><engcorp2></engcorp2></attview><attautid>168</attautid></newatts>
<firstl><l ln="1        ">When we first touched</l></firstl>
<l ln="2        ">And, to use a word</l>
<l ln="3        ">That sounds old&hyphen;fashioned now&mdash;kissed</l>
<l ln="4        ">Morning was music, night</l>
<l ln="5        ">Love In A Mist.</l>
<l ln="6        ">Now with glaucous eyes we glower</l>
<l ln="7        ">Resentful and unheeding,</l>
<l ln="8        ">And cruelly ignore each others needs&mdash;</l>
<l ln="9        ">Love Lies Bleeding.</l>
<poemcopy>&copy; Copyright material reproduced under licence from Carcanet Press Ltd.</poemcopy>
</poem>
</div2>
